{
  "doc_id": "18792",
  "text": "We have shown that equivalence of LT A s relative to a given DTA B can be decided in polynomial time. For that, we considered total transducers only, but defined the domain of allowed input trees separately by means of the DTA. This does not impose any restriction of generality, since any (possibly partial) linear deterministic top-down tree transducer can be translated in polynomial time to a corresponding total LT A together with a corresponding DTA (see, e.g., [CITATION_1] ). The required constructions for LT A s which we have presented here, turn out to be more general than the constructions provided in [CITATION_2] since they apply to transducers which may not only output symbols a ∈ A, but also their inverses a − . At the same time, they are simpler and easier to be proven correct due to the combinatorial and algebraic properties provided by the free group.",
